</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=smallcutepuppy>smallcutepuppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 630<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/21/02 10:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro  Maitenance</span><hr size=1> I really like my Blood Point (10/21) for aggro. 80 point lifetap seems to piss them off pretty well. I like it a lot better than my old Lammy. Too bad it looks just like a rusty dagger. I have a Longsword of Ethereal Energy (16+5magic/29) in offhand, might not seem ideal on the speed front but it does so much damage I rarely have a problem holding aggro in a similarly-leveled group. 15 AC and +12 dex (to help with my dagger procs) is also nice. (Getting aggro from a 60 rogue after she double backstabs right at the start, that's another matter of course. But I've usually managed to grab it back in time for her to get some more stabs in.)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1550<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/21/02 2:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Bloodpoint is nice ..</span><hr size=1> .. and if you can find something to snare, slow, or dot, that works well, too; eg. fungus glands are nice for maintaining raid agro but are now expensive to recharge.  Wavecrasher (from SG) and Willsapper (from DN) are both very nice, but also tough to get for you at your level.<br>
<br>
There's also a hammer from Lynuga's quest that clicks walking sleep.  It's only got 5 charges and is lore, but it's fairly cheap to recharge if you have a second account to hold the extra.  It's also enough of a slow that it does a fair job helping a warrior solo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dalninil@firionavie>Dalninil</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 707<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/21/02 4:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bloodpoint is nice ..</span><hr size=1> Agro is also about positioning your position vs the person you're trying to taunt off of.<br>
<br>
I'm currently main handing a 13/23 that proc's force strike<br>
179point dd with stun component 41% haste and eyepatch with a self cast 65pnt proc on top of that.<br>
<br>
That being said i've grouped with 2 warriors that are running the same setup you are that have been able to maintain agro.<br>
<br>
Due to  them keeping in close, keeping the kicks going and keeping pressing in.<br>
<br>
And i wait *shrug* 2 or 3 seconds and strike at near max range.<br>
<br>
Consider that  both evasive and defensive drop your melee output ( and taunt )<br>
<br>
Agro is as much your job as not getting agro is there job.<br>
<br>
Any equally equiped hybrid,melee damage class can pull agro off a warrior, they should realized however that they aren't doing what they are suppose to be doing and that's letting you tank stuff.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarkellraven>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blessed of Bristlebane</span><br>  Posts: 1737<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/21/02 4:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bloodpoint is nice ..</span><hr size=1> The Ice Forged Shackles proc is worthless for agro, or anything else, so forget about that one.<br>
<br>
Stay close to the mobs.  So many warriors forget this one.  Stay VERY close.  Proximity agro means a lot.<br>
<br>
