</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sordail>Sordail</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 11/22/02 11:24:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=braellarth>Braellarth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 342<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/22/02 12:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro  Maitenance</span><hr size=1> IMHO Lammy + Jbom is a good damage combo for your lv..... but the pits for taunting.<br>
<br>
Had a couple of people useing these - i hate it!!! pretty much <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Forced</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> me to feign death two times a fight and not cast any dps increasing spell....... i would never hit the taunt button and be useing a &quot;Beserker sword of revaij&quot; at the time, and i was consistantly pulling agro and holding without hitting taunt, if i cast snare i h would have agro for the whole fight after a few swings, forcing me to feign death and drop agro for a few seconds - then my hits would start working up and i would grab agro again, this consistantly happened with warriors useing those two wepons.<br>
