<br>
Once kick acquires a stun component (I forget what level, 54-56ish?) I don't know which becomes more useful, but I'd still bank on bash, just 'cause it's capped so much higher so you'll hit more. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=exeter1>Exeter1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(11/24/02 1:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=165.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Aggro  Maitenance</span><hr size=1> Hmmm<br>
<br>
I have heard it said there is blood aggro that accumulates elevating your position in the hate list.  This is caused by weapons with good damage/delay.<br>
<br>
However I am taking a dim view of procs.  I have heard it said that procs - when they proc - help with aggro for that round - but do not carry over to the next round - do not build your position in the hate list over time.<br>
<br>
Formerly I used two black acrylia weapons that proced for lifetap (my dex 150-255 depending upon buffs).  However, switching to crescent blade of luclin (primary) and priceless velium spear seems to be much more effective.<br>
<br>
Opinions?<br>
