<br>
Step 1: Group with a REALLY aggro class.  SK's are the best bet, naturally. Monks with stun procs, or chain stunning pallies are a good choice as well (since you can group with those icky pallies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Step 2: If you choose an SK, have them cast the voice line on you.  It adds anywhere from 2% (at 34 I think) to 10% (at 60) aggro to you.  It really does add up after a while.  At first, I was loathe to lose a spell slot for it (Recast is 9-10 minutes, lasts 10 minutes).  However, it definately allows sub-aggroing warriors the extra hate they need to keep a mob peeled on them.<br>
<br>
Step 3: Have the super-aggro class do what they do best: Super aggro.  For me, best results seem to be Spears+snare+snare, maybe even terror spells if you like that line. Personally, I use clinging darkness, fast cast and massive hate, even on resists.  So I'm obviously now getting beat on pretty hard.  This mob hates me an amazing amount.  I couldn't get this thing off of me if I tried.  Now here comes the fun part...<br>
<br>
Step 4: Warrior (this is you) presses the Taunt key.  You now have super aggro+1.<br>
<br>
Step 5: Aggro class stops attacking for a second (alternatively can FD).  You start attacking full on.<br>
<br>
Step 6: Enjoy having aggro the whole fight!<br>
<br>
Sometimes your first taunt doesn't take, it may take a little bit, but in the end you will not lose aggro barring something ungodly.  Try it out, see if that doesn't help keep things stuck on you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
